There was a mad rush today as Kenyans tried to beat the 8 pm deadline Sunday to travel in and out of Nairobi, Kajiado, Machakos, Kiambu, and Nakuru counties. this after the government spokesperson Cyrus Oguna made clarifications to the directive given by President Uhuru Kenyatta on Friday. KTN senior reporter Geff Kirui looks at the mad rush within the zoned areas as Kenyans hoped to beat the deadline.